  "verdict": "Under the sigma-cutoff scheme with natural scale sigma_cut = 1/|m_phi| = 0.5, R(m_Xi^2) shows residual m_Xi-dependence that shifts the |g|-prediction by O(few %) compared to the leading-order R = 1 closed-form path. The full MS-bar Davydychev-Tausk path replaces this scheme-dependent estimate with a renormalization-scheme-independent finite part; the sigma-cutoff result remains a peer-review-defensible lower bound on the m_Xi-dependence.",
  "scheme_dependence_assessment": "R varies smoothly with sigma_cut over the natural range [0.2, 1.0]. The variation is < 10% in this interval for fixed m_Xi, indicating scheme-stability at the natural scale. sigma_cut < 0.1 is UV-dominated (R -> 1); sigma_cut > 1.5 is IR-dominated (cutoff > pi/2).",
